  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Understanding and Enhancing Preparedness and Response to Risks of Disaster Displacement in the Pacific</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to work with the Governments of the Solomon Islands, Tonga, and Vanuatu to reduce the disaster displacement risk to vulnerable communities in their countries. This project will be implemented as part of a broader program led by the Internal Displacement Monitoring Centre (IDMC), and in conjunction with the Platform for Disaster Displacement.  The outcome of the project is strengthening the disaster displacement responses of the Solomon Islands, Vanuatu, Tonga, and Marshall Islands&#x2019; governments and to reduce the disaster displacement risk to vulnerable communities in their countries. The end result would be to reduce the vulnerability to disasters for at-risk communities of Solomon Islands, Vanuatu, Tonga, and Marshall Islands&#x2019; in a sustainable and comprehensive way.</narrative>
  </description>
